[h3 id=Introduction 
	" Introduction
	$LF
]h3
[h4 id=IAmGettingThisErrorToRunThisApplicationYouFirstMustInstallOneOfTheFollowingVersionsOfTheNetFrameworkV4030319 
	" I am getting this error: "To run this application, you first must install one of the following versions of the .NET framework: v4.0.30319"
	$LF
]h4
[div class=p 
	"You computer did not have .NET Framework 4 installed on it and BizHawk requires this framework.  The 
	[a href=https://github.com/TASEmulators/BizHawk-Prereqs/releases rel=noopener external nofollow 
		"Prereqs installer
	]a
	" provided will fix this.  You can also get this from 
	[a href=http://www.microsoft.com/download/en/details.aspx?id=17851 Microsoft rel=noopener external nofollow 
		"http://www.microsoft.com/download/en/details.aspx?id=17851 Microsoft
	]a
	$LF
]div
[h4 id=GamesAreRunningWayTooFastEvenWithConfigSpeedSkipLimitFramerateOn 
	" Games are running way too fast even with Config -> Speed/Skip -> Limit Framerate On
	$LF
]h4
[div class=p 
	"Your computer hardware may not be accurately reporting time.  See 
	[a href=http://support.microsoft.com/kb/895980 rel=noopener external nofollow 
		"this article
	]a
	" to see if this is your issue.  Adding /usepmtimer to your boot.ini may fix this.  Refer 
	[a href=http://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/library/ms940839%28v=winembedded.5%29.aspx rel=noopener external nofollow 
		"this
	]a
	" on how to add multiple boot configs (do this temporarily in case this line causes a boot failure)
	$LF
]div
[h4 id=WhatDoesBizhawkMean 
	" What does BizHawk mean?
	$LF
]h4
[div class=p 
	"BizHawk is Hawk Biz.
	$LF
]div
[h3 id=CrashesAndSuch 
	" Crashes And Such
	$LF
]h3
[h4 id=OutOfMemoryErrorsWhileRecordingMovies 
	" Out of memory errors while recording movies
	$LF
]h4
[div class=p 
	"Use config > customize > Store movie working data on disk instead of RAM - This will eliminate most of the possible out of memory errors by simply not using RAM. This option has been well-validated.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"-or-
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"Use config > customize > Store movie working data in extended > 1GB Ram - This option is useful on 64bit systems with >=8GB of RAM - `AWE` is employed to access more memory than normal in a 32bit process. As mentioned, this has not yet been well validated and may require admin permissions.
	$LF
]div
[h3 id=MemoryManipulation 
	" Memory Manipulation
	$LF
]h3
[h4 id=IMTryingToCheatPokeFreezeAMemoryAddressButItKeepsChanging 
	" I'm trying to cheat/poke/freeze a memory address, but it keeps changing
	$LF
]h4
[div class=p 
	"Bizhawk can only overwrite your address once per frame, so if the game changes it more frequently, you'll have to use memory write callbacks to track when the game does so, to overwrite it yourself right after that.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"But since some callbacks happen before the event, and some happen after (depending on the core), you may have to change CPU registers instead, where the value initially comes from upon the memory write.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"Note that not every Bizhawk core implements memory callbacks and register editing.
	$LF
]div
[h3 id=RunningGames 
	" Running Games
	$LF
]h3
[h4 id=IGetTheErrorYouAreMissingTheNeededFirmwareFilesToLoadThisRom 
	" I get the error "You are missing the needed firmware files to load this Rom"
	$LF
]h4
[div class=p 
	"This is due to not having the Firmware/BIOS file(s) in the Firmware folder.
	$LF
]div
[h4 id=WhereCanIFindTheFirmwareFiles 
	" Where can I find the Firmware files?
	$LF
]h4
[div class=p 
	"You need to dump them from the hardware.  They are not legally download able due to being copyrighted.
	$LF
]div
